THE STUDENT PILOT WAS FLYING HER FIRST SUPERVISED SOLO. SHE LANDED ON 
RUNWAY 20 WITH A WIND FROM 240 DEGREES AT 9 KTS. WITNESSES SAID SHE 
FLARED HIGH AND THE AIRCRAFT BOUNCED DURING TOUCHDOWN. ON THE THIRD 
BOUNCE, THE NOSE GEAR COLLAPSED, THEN THE AIRCRAFT SKIDDED TO A STOP ON ITS 
NOSED. 
THE PILOT'S IMPROPER FLARE AND IMPROPER RECOVERY FROM A BOUNCED 
LANDING, WHICH RESULTED IN A HARD LANDING. 
